column5: ahhh, nyc.  in new york, you can be ANYTHING you want, and nobody cares.  nice.

.... another 95 degree day.... lolo...  just about killed the kids...  heres some pictures from today...   Heres Jaden eating some frog.... at a great Vietnamise restaurant in Chinatown...   Heres a picture we took today at the World Trade Center site...  I got all choked up just standing there... it was the most moving experience I've had in a while..... I don't want to have a political discussion here... but standing there may change a few opinions...   We went down and jumped on the Staton Island Ferry and too a ride (FREE!!) accross the bottom of Manhattan to Jersey and got to snap some pics of Lady Liberty along the way..  On the way back to the motel we walked through little italy...   Were gonna go walk around Times Square....  tommorow. hopefully its Central Park and the Museum of Natural History before catching the train back to Saratoga Springs!

Looks like the trip is really adding a whole new perspective to your thoughts... Some amazing pictures but even more noticible is the amazing family time you are sharing.  Something can be said for kids who will order food when they can not really read the menu...  Thanks for the pictures... you certainly know how to share a vacation!  Cheers,  jen
Sure is noisy.....
TJ, you thed you were going to call me before going to the Gay Pride Parade!
What is that girl swallowing  Looks busy!!  Joey
going to be tough to catch fish there.  cheers!
Must have been a heck of a party.
....Looks crowded.
Just remember "aspirin has many uses but it  will not bring a dead hooker back to life" be careful in the big city bud.   Art

aplumma... thats why we brought tylenol.... and yes .. fish will be hard to come by... were right in times square for 3 days for some sightseeing before we head back in the bush...  saw a play on broadway last nite with the kids... FANTASTIC!!  Today is tour bus sight seeing... they have these walkon-andoff double decker buses we will be riding them fo a couple of days...  sposed to be 35 degreees here today.... uhhhhhhgggggg  Slowpoke...  dude... didnt ya get my message... they cancelled your membership... they said you were a bit too committed to the movement!!
Looks like Home to Me !!! Just head to south for some stripers!!!
Quick TJ.......get out the pink tutu, you'll blend right in!  lol   Have a wonderful time!!!

LOL.. ill look for the tutu ... but i dont think i packed it.   Jaden Getting her palm read.....  apparenlty I better get her dowry ready...   Really cool way to do beef over the open fire.... hmm  gives me ideas!!   Umm i need a TV like this for the camp.....   This would be good toooo...  were heading here for supper!!!  Kids should love it!!
They got some Huge Large Mouth in central park pond, I hope you got some time to try it out.
Glad you guys are having a good time...the restaurant looks pretty cool...a couple of lucky kids you got there  Maureen
The parents are lucky too, Moe. To paraphrase....the more they worked at being a family, the luckier they got.
Did you see the naked cowboy? He is always down there.  The first time I ever was there I was shocked how much smaller it is in real life then on the TV
NOT a fan of NYC.....yuck!  dk

LOL..  i gotta tell ya.. theres no way I could live here..  but.. its an unbielevable place to visit...  and ill go have a look for the cowboy...  supposed to be 35 and sunny here....  heres pics from yesterday...

Just pop open a man hole cover, drop a ham sandwich down the hole, fells like ice fishin, and get ready for a "CHUD" to grab it and run! (CHUD - Cannibalistic Humanoid Underground Dweller!) They put up on heck of a fight, but are not recommended table fare! HH
Well, at least he went to church   How was the restaurant TJ?  Joey

A couple of things....  the resaurant was great... it was cool fo us, but the kids really enjoyed it... they had all sorts of actors walking around and a ton of cool animatronic devices that talked to you... very cool..  also.. there is a cop on every corner here now and it sure isnt the same place it was last time I was here about 15 years ago...  heres some pics from the resaurant ..and then we gotta get going... its empire state building, statue of liberty and WTC day today!!
ROFLMAO.........    Umm... do i need a licence for them??
The night deposit slot for the mens' brains must be larger I guess eh? *runs fer cover*
NO licence required TJ... it's a "put and take" resource! HH
Ya, you better run shorty, hope those legs can carry you fast enough....
Naked cowboy going to the drag races..............
